    "Body": " Director of Pricing Analytics at Overstock.com Inc. Midvale, UT 84047 ?? About the Job Director of Pricing Analytics Job Summary: The Director of Pricing Analytics leads??a team of analysts in strategy, processes, and related reporting and metrics that support innovation and efficiency gains across the entire company. Focusing on the company\u2019s target customer segments and brand pillars as our innovative guardrails, this role will be responsible for leading the execution of customer profitability through pricing and value-capturing activities at both strategic and tactical levels in a variety of channels. Reporting directly to the Vice President of Analytics of Overstock Retail, the candidate will work with executives and senior leaders across all areas of Overstock.com to identify and develop pricing models and strategies that maximize price and margin opportunities.?? This role will focus on elevating the company\u2019s existing data and analytics to automate and scale capabilities in order to create increased efficiencies throughout the business and resolve some of the more advanced problems, such as price and promotion elasticity models for millions of products. As Director of Pricing Analytics, the candidate will have analysts reporting directly to them, and will work closely across verticals to ensure that the team\u2019s work is aligned with the current and future goals of the company. Responsibilities: Provides leadership and project management, ensuring initiatives are delivered on-time and deliver operational and financial objectives Develop and manage KPI\u2019s to monitor performance, providing price recommendations and guardrails for deals and promotions. Managing our price check process to ensure that our competitive data is actionable Communicates effectively across the organization regarding profitable opportunities and key pricing insights Demonstrates knowledge of e-commerce economics, financial modeling techniques, and related pricing and promotion strategies Analyze the company\u2019s competitive environment to identify opportunities to drive revenue and profit increases.?? Develop, implement, and maintain pricing programs designed to enhance revenue and margin Forecast brand profitability based on pricing and marketing strategies, industry trends, and competition Work across the organization to provide analytical pricing structures Develop expertise with our current systems and tools to enhance execution of strategies Direct and manage teams while also directly working on tasks assigned by manager and upper management Coach analysts in analytics methodologies, strategies, career development and conduct employee training and evaluation. Provide support during the hiring and onboarding process Assess pricing analytics roadmaps to determine staffing needs to effectively achieve objectives Introduce and update processes in collaboration with team and developers Deliver world class analytical delivery work in pricing analytics?? Job Requirements: Required 7+ years relevant work experience Knowledge and experience with pricing models, processes, systems, and controls General retail/online business knowledge \u200band the Scientific Method and application in business Proficiency in statistical analysis, data mining, and software including SQL, R, Python Working knowledge of related technologies, databases, tracking implantation, and workflows Track record of leading organizational transformation and analytical projects Basic understanding of marketing and financial concepts Strong intellectual curiosity combined with a knack for recognizing correlations, trends, and statistical irregularities Experienced using tools such as SAS, SPSS, Adobe Analytics, and Google Analytics Interpreting and understanding test results Ability to work with product managers, marketers, developers, ETC. Project management experience Preferred E-commerce retail pricing experience Refined presentation skills and story d